===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Li Shoukui (2015) notes that {{lang|zh|šĺé}} may potentially be a corruption of {{zh-l|*ŚĪé}} that later adapted an etymologically unrelated reading and meaning, on the basis that ''[[w:Shuowen Jiezi|Shuowen Jiezi]]'' writes that the origin of {{lang|zh|šĺé}} is unknown, that {{zh-l|*Śįł}} and {{zh-l|*šļļ}} were occasionally used interchangeably in [[oracle bone script]] writing, and that given {{zh-l|*ŚįŅ}} was often corrupted as {{lang|zh|‚ŅįšļĽśįī}} in ancient writing, one cannot rule out that {{lang|zh|šĺé}} doesn't follow the same potential origin.<ref name=lishoukui>{{cite-journal|author=Li Shoukui (śĚéŚģąŚ•é)|month=April|year=2015|title=‚ÄúŚĪé‚ÄĚŤąá‚ÄúŚĺôšĻčŚŹ§śĖá‚ÄĚŤÄÉ|trans-title=On the ancient glyphs of ‚ÄúŚĪé‚ÄĚ and ‚ÄúŚĺô‚ÄĚ|url=http://www.ctwx.tsinghua.edu.cn/publish/cetrp/6830/20180509193448059149355/1525865710208.pdf|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210111041619/http://www.ctwx.tsinghua.edu.cn/publish/cetrp/6830/20180509193448059149355/1525865710208.pdf|archivedate=11 January 2021|journal=ŚáļŚúüśĖáÁćĽ|volume=6|pages=154-162|publisher=Tsinghua University|accessdate=11 January 2021}}</ref>

